The paper deals with motion planning for an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) in a cluttered urban landscape, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) for obstacle detection and avoidance. The algorithm proposed in the paper involves the use of a Markov Decision Process (MDP) for determining the optimal action to be taken by the UAV, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a Dubins vehicle model for the UAV, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm in a simulation environment, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves training and testing a model.
